Toyoka 16-Nov-17 10:10 AM
vmat is the file that references the vtexs and stuff
idealsl you want to recreate the vmat
ideally*
I don't think overriding individual vtexs will work
it may also be because the vtexs are located in different directories from the vmats
so placing them in the same firectory won't always work
you can check the references the vmat uses in the asset browser when you click on the vmat https://i.imgur.com/oWKp8VG.png
you will probably have to replicate the exact naming of these .vtexs (yes, with numbers/letters too) as well
trouble with that is
they change every time valve updates that particular material/texture
so you have two choices: a) keep changing the vtex name with each update b) recreate the vmat and avoid changing the vtex
both have their ups/downs
I'd say if you're only changing a part of the material, stick with changing the vmat and updating the name every time the material is updated
because you for sure won't have all the textures needed to fully recreate the material (especially if it is particularly complex)
even if you open the material up in the material editor and screenshot the compiled textures
which are usually shown in the wrong format anyway
but yea, it's a bunch of work either way
